		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Amory Lovins</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<table class="infobox biography vcard vevent" cellspacing="5" style="width: 22em; text-align: left; font-size: 88%; line-height: 1.5em; width:22em; font-size:95%; text-align:left;">
<tr>
<td colspan="2" class="fn summary" style="text-align:center; font-size: 125%; font-weight: bold; text-align:center; font-size:125%;"><b>Amory Lovins</b></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan="2" class="" style="text-align:center; padding:4pt; line-height:1.25em; text-align:center; font-size:8pt;"><a href="/wiki/File:Amory_Lovins.jpg" class="image" title="Amory Lovins.jpg"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/96/Amory_Lovins.jpg/225px-Amory_Lovins.jpg" width="225" height="221" border="0" /></a><br />
<div style="padding-top:2pt;"><span style="">Amory Lovins</span></div>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th style="padding:0.2em 1.0em 0.2em 0.2em; background:transparent; line-height:1.2em; text-align:left; font-size:90%;">Born</th>
<td class="" style="padding:0.2em; line-height:1.3em; vertical-align:middle; font-size:90%;">November 13, 1947<span style="display:none">&#160;(<span class="dtstart bday">1947-11-13</span>)</span><br />
<a href="/wiki/Washington,_DC" title="Washington, DC" class="mw-redirect">Washington, DC</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th style="padding:0.2em 1.0em 0.2em 0.2em; background:transparent; line-height:1.2em; text-align:left; font-size:90%;">Occupation</th>
<td class="role" style="padding:0.2em; line-height:1.3em; vertical-align:middle; font-size:90%;"><a href="/wiki/Environmentalist" title="Environmentalist" class="mw-redirect">environmentalist</a>, <a href="/wiki/Physicist" title="Physicist">physicist</a></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p><b>Amory Bloch Lovins</b> (born November 13, 1947 in <a href="/wiki/Washington,_DC" title="Washington, DC" class="mw-redirect">Washington, DC</a>) is Chairman and Chief Scientist of the <a href="/wiki/Rocky_Mountain_Institute" title="Rocky Mountain Institute">Rocky Mountain Institute</a>, a <a href="/wiki/MacArthur_Fellowship" title="MacArthur Fellowship" class="mw-redirect">MacArthur Fellowship</a> recipient (1993), and author and co-author of many books on <a href="/wiki/Renewable_energy" title="Renewable energy">renewable energy</a> and <a href="/wiki/Energy_efficiency" title="Energy efficiency" class="mw-redirect">energy efficiency</a>.</p>
<p>Lovins has worked professionally as an <a href="/wiki/Environmentalist" title="Environmentalist" class="mw-redirect">environmentalist</a> and an advocate for a "<a href="/wiki/Soft_energy_path" title="Soft energy path">soft energy path</a>" for the <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">United States</a> and other nations. He has promoted energy-use and energy-production concepts based on <a href="/wiki/Energy_conservation" title="Energy conservation">energy conservation</a>, efficiency, the use of renewable sources of energy, and on generation of energy at or near the site where the energy is actually used. His books include <i><a href="/wiki/Winning_the_Oil_Endgame" title="Winning the Oil Endgame">Winning the Oil Endgame</a></i>, <i>Factor Four</i>, and <i><a href="/wiki/Natural_Capitalism" title="Natural Capitalism" class="mw-redirect">Natural Capitalism</a></i>. In the 1990s, his work with the Rocky Mountain Institute included the design of an ultra-efficient automobile, the <a href="/wiki/Hypercar" title="Hypercar">Hypercar</a>.</p>
<p>Lovins has provided expert testimony in eight countries and more than 20 US states, briefed 19 heads of state, and published 29 books.</p>
